occer.com/ Beach Soccer Worldwide]\n\n{{Mundialito de Clubes}}\n{{International Beach Soccer}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2011 Mundialito De Clubes}}\n[[Category:Mundialito de Clubes]]\n[[Category:2011 in beach soccer]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name = I Mundialito de Clubes\n| year = \n| other_titles =\n| image = Mundialito-de-clubes.jpg\n| size = 250px\n| country = Brazil\n| dates = 19\u201326 March 2011\n| num_teams = 10\n| confederations = 3\n| venues = 1\n| cities = 1\n| champion_other = \n| count = \n| second_other = \n| third_other = \n| fourth_other = \n| matches = \n| goals = \n| attendance =\n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| updated = \n| prevseason = \n| nextseason = [[2012 Mundialito de Clubes squads|2012]]\n}}\nThese are the rosters of the ten participating teams at the inaugural [[2011 Mundialito de Clubes|Mundialito de Clubes]] (or Club World Cup) beach soccer tournament that will take place at a temporary beach soccer stadium at [[Represa de Guarapiranga]], a reservoir located in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]] from 19\u201326 March 2011. The first nine were drafted at the Official Draft, with the tenth player added by [[Beach Soccer Worldwide]] 48 hours later.<ref>[http://www.beachsoccer.com/news/212 Rosters].</ref>\n\n== Rosters of Participating Teams ==\n\n=== [[FC Barcelona (beach soccer)|Barcelona]] ===\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! width=\"750\" colspan=\"3\"|'''Coach: [[Ramiro Figueiras Amarelle|Ramiro Amarelle]]'''\n|-\n| width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|ESP}} Juanma || width=\"250\" rowspan=\"6\"| <center>{{flagicon|size=40px|ESP}}<br><big>'''[[FC Barcelona (beach soccer)|Barcelona]]</big></center> || width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|POL}} Witold Ziober\n|-\n| width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|ESP}} Javier Torres || width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|BRA}} Fred\n|-\n| width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|ESP}} Nico || width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|JPN}} Tomoya Ginoza\n|-\n| width=\"250\"|{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Andrey Bukhlitskiy|Andrei Bukhlitskiy]] 